ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIB.name: ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIB

revisions.description: This revision involves the following changes to table cvpdnTunnelExtTable. 1] Deprecated cvpdnTunnelBytesIn, cvpdnTunnelBytesOut 32-bit counters. 2] Added new OIDs cvpdnTunnelBytesIn64, cvpdnTunnelBytesOut64 64-bit counters.
Corrected the format of LAST-UPDATED and REVISION fields.

ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-vpdn@cisco.com
ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIB.description: Cisco VPDN management MIB extension Module. This MIB is a supplement to CISCO-VPDN-MGMT-MIB.my. The main enhancements are: 1. Added cvpdnTunnelExtTable for more tunnel information. 2. Added cvpdnSessionExtTable for more session information. Please notice that objects in CvpdnTunnelEntry and CvpdnTunnelSessionEntry are still applicable to the corresponding tunnels and sessions.

cvpdnTunnelExtTable.name: cvpdnTunnelExtTable
cvpdnTunnelExtTable.description: Vpn Tunnel table includes all tunnels configured.

cvpdnTunnelExtEntry.name: cvpdnTunnelExtEntry
cvpdnTunnelExtEntry.description: Please notice that this entry is a supplement to CvpdnTunnelEntry in CISCO-VPDN-MGMT-MIB for the L2TP tunnels. Here more objects are used to reflect tunnel parameters. Included are tunnel statistics, UDP port numbers and the time of last state (cvpdnTunnelState) change.

cvpdnTunnelLocalPort.name: cvpdnTunnelLocalPort
cvpdnTunnelLocalPort.description: The local port number of the tunnel. This is the UDP port of the interface at the local end of the tunnel.

cvpdnTunnelRemotePort.name: cvpdnTunnelRemotePort
cvpdnTunnelRemotePort.description: The remote port number of the tunnel. This is the UDP port of the interface at the remote end of the tunnel.

cvpdnTunnelLastChange.name: cvpdnTunnelLastChange
cvpdnTunnelLastChange.description: The time of last state change reflected in cvpdnTunnelState.

cvpdnTunnelPacketsOut.name: cvpdnTunnelPacketsOut
cvpdnTunnelPacketsOut.description: The total number of output packets through the tunnel.

cvpdnTunnelBytesOut.name: cvpdnTunnelBytesOut
cvpdnTunnelBytesOut.description: The total number of output bytes through the tunnel. cvpdnTunnelBytesOut object is superseded by cvpdnTunnelBytesOut64.

cvpdnTunnelPacketsIn.name: cvpdnTunnelPacketsIn
cvpdnTunnelPacketsIn.description: The total number of input packets through the tunnel.

cvpdnTunnelBytesIn.name: cvpdnTunnelBytesIn
cvpdnTunnelBytesIn.description: The total number of input bytes through the tunnel. cvpdnTunnelBytesIn object is superseded by cvpdnTunnelBytesIn64.

cvpdnTunnelBytesIn64.name: cvpdnTunnelBytesIn64
cvpdnTunnelBytesIn64.description: The total number of input bytes through the tunnel.

cvpdnTunnelBytesOut64.name: cvpdnTunnelBytesOut64
cvpdnTunnelBytesOut64.description: The total number of output bytes through the tunnel.

cvpdnSessionExtTable.name: cvpdnSessionExtTable
cvpdnSessionExtTable.description: Session table includes all Sessions currently active.

cvpdnSessionExtEntry.name: cvpdnSessionExtEntry
cvpdnSessionExtEntry.description: Please notice that this entry is a supplement to CvpdnTunnelSessionEntry in CISCO-VPDN-MGMT-MIB for the L2TP sessions. Here more objects are used to reflect session parameters.

cvpdnSessionRemoteId.name: cvpdnSessionRemoteId
cvpdnSessionRemoteId.description: The remote end ID of an active VPN tunnel user session.

cvpdnSessionInterfaceName.name: cvpdnSessionInterfaceName
cvpdnSessionInterfaceName.description: The interface name (description) of the user session.

cvpdnSessionLastChange.name: cvpdnSessionLastChange
cvpdnSessionLastChange.description: The time stamp of last change in cvpdnTunnelSessionState.

cvpdnSessionOutOfOrderPackets.name: cvpdnSessionOutOfOrderPackets
cvpdnSessionOutOfOrderPackets.description: The total number of out of order packets through this active user session.

cvpdnSessionSequencing.name: cvpdnSessionSequencing
cvpdnSessionSequencing.description: The object indicates whether sequencing is on or not.

cvpdnSessionSendSequence.name: cvpdnSessionSendSequence
cvpdnSessionSendSequence.description: This object contains the next send sequence number for for this session.

cvpdnSessionRecvSequence.name: cvpdnSessionRecvSequence
cvpdnSessionRecvSequence.description: This object contains the next receive sequence number expected to be received on this session.

cvpdnSessionRemoteSendSequence.name: cvpdnSessionRemoteSendSequence
cvpdnSessionRemoteSendSequence.description: This object contains the next send sequence number for for this session.

cvpdnSessionRemoteRecvSequence.name: cvpdnSessionRemoteRecvSequence
cvpdnSessionRemoteRecvSequence.description: This object contains the next receive sequence number expected to be received on this session.

cvpdnSessionSentZLB.name: cvpdnSessionSentZLB
cvpdnSessionSentZLB.description: This object returns the total number of Zero Length Body acknowledgement packets transmitted on this session.

cvpdnSessionRecvZLB.name: cvpdnSessionRecvZLB
cvpdnSessionRecvZLB.description: This object returns the total number of Zero Length Body acknowlegement payload packets received for this session.

cvpdnSessionSentRBits.name: cvpdnSessionSentRBits
cvpdnSessionSentRBits.description: This object contains the total number of sequence number resets (payload packets with the R-bit set) received on this session.

cvpdnSessionRecvRBits.name: cvpdnSessionRecvRBits
cvpdnSessionRecvRBits.description: This object contains the total number of sequence number resets (payload packets with the R-bit set) received on this session.

cvpdnSessionLocalWindowSize.name: cvpdnSessionLocalWindowSize
cvpdnSessionLocalWindowSize.description: This object returns the local send window size for this session. If the value of the object cvpdnSessionSequencing is false, then this object should return value zero.

cvpdnSessionRemoteWindowSize.name: cvpdnSessionRemoteWindowSize
cvpdnSessionRemoteWindowSize.description: This object returns the initial remote send window size for this session. If the value of the object cvpdnSessionSequencingState is none(1) then this object should not be interpreted.

cvpdnSessionCurrentWindowSize.name: cvpdnSessionCurrentWindowSize
cvpdnSessionCurrentWindowSize.description: This object returns the local send window size for this session. If the value of the object cvpdnSessionSequencingState is none(1) then this object should not be interpreted.

cvpdnSessionMinimumWindowSize.name: cvpdnSessionMinimumWindowSize
cvpdnSessionMinimumWindowSize.description: This object returns the initial remote send window size for this session. If the value of the object cvpdnSessionSequencingState is none(1) then this object should not be interpreted.

cvpdnSessionATOTimeouts.name: cvpdnSessionATOTimeouts
cvpdnSessionATOTimeouts.description: The object reflects the current adaptive timeout the system is using.

cvpdnSessionOutGoingQueueSize.name: cvpdnSessionOutGoingQueueSize
cvpdnSessionOutGoingQueueSize.description: The object reflects the queue size of out going queue.

cvpdnSessionCalculationType.name: cvpdnSessionCalculationType
cvpdnSessionCalculationType.description: The object reflects the round trip time calculation type.

cvpdnSessionAdaptiveTimeOut.name: cvpdnSessionAdaptiveTimeOut
cvpdnSessionAdaptiveTimeOut.description: The object reflects the configured session adaptive timeout.

cvpdnSessionRoundTripTime.name: cvpdnSessionRoundTripTime
cvpdnSessionRoundTripTime.description: The object reflects the round trip time.

cvpdnSessionPktProcessingDelay.name: cvpdnSessionPktProcessingDelay
cvpdnSessionPktProcessingDelay.description: The object reflects the number of packets in processing delay for this session.

cvpdnSessionZLBTime.name: cvpdnSessionZLBTime
cvpdnSessionZLBTime.description: The object reflects the zero length body time interval.

ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIBBasicCompliance.name: ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIBBasicCompliance
ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIBBasicCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco VPN Management MIB. ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIBBasicCompliance is superseded by ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIBBasicComplianceV2.

ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIBBasicComplianceV2.name: ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIBBasicComplianceV2
ciscoVpdnMgmtExtMIBBasicComplianceV2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco VPN Management MIB Version 2.

cvpdnTunnelExtGroup.name: cvpdnTunnelExtGroup
cvpdnTunnelExtGroup.description: VPN Tunnel Group. cvpdnTunnelExtGroup is superseded by cvpdnTunnelExtGroupV2
